    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/630.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A loan agreement with an Anglo-French-Belgian syndicate was signed yesterday by
                    the Chinese Ministry of Finance for 150,000,000 francs; it is reported to be for
                    ninety years at 96, with 4 per cent rebate, interest 6 per cent, to be converted
                    to 5 per cent later. An advance is to be made within fourteen days, first issue
                    in ninety days. Ratification by secret edict to-day is reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
